tation, which makes unit testing sufficient. Integration or system-level tests would add confidence but aren't strictly necessary if the mocks accurately reflect the real API's behavior.\n\nI'm satisfied with unit as the minimum. Now I'll structure the final JSON output.\n\nLet me verify the probability distributions sum correctly across all scenarios—checking that each behavior's weights total 1.0 across all test levels. All seven scenarios check out, each summing to exactly 1.0.\n\nNow I'll structure this using the uredOutput tool.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13708,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13708},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e88b46e3-e7ef-4734-a998-56cefbe3074a","uuid":"6345082c-8651-4b7c-a232-e851972dd556"}
